[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rail delays through Reading after man hit by train

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Rail passengers faced delays when a man was hit by a train at Crowthorne, near Reading.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Great Western Railway (GWR) services were suspended between Guildford and Reading shortly after 06:15 BST.
The man suffered life-threatening and life-changing injuries when he was struck near Wellington College, South Central Ambulance said.
GWR said passengers faced delays of up to an hour before services resumed with some residual disruption.
